{{Infobox artwork | title = Seattle Fishermen's Memorial | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | image = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | artist = Ronald Petty | catalogue = | year = <!-- If after 1583 CE, use {{start date|YYYY}} --> | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | type = Sculpture | material = [[Bronze sculpture|Bronze]], concrete | subject = | height_metric = <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | height_imperial = 30 | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = m <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = ft <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = "Well maintained" (1994) | city = [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], United States | museum = | accession = | coordinates = {{Coord|47.65589|-122.380643|type:landmark_region:US-WA|display=inline,title}} | owner = | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''''Seattle Fishermen's Memorial''''', or '''''Fisherman's Memorial''''', is an outdoor sculpture by Ronald Petty, installed at [[Fishermen's Terminal]] in [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], in the United States.<ref name=SI>{{cite web|title=Seattle Fishermen's Memorial, (sculpture).|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!317189~!0#focus|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]|accessdate=February 10, 2016}}</ref> The monument was designed in 1987 and dedicated in October 1988. It commemorates Seattle fisherman who died since 1900.
==Description== [[File:Seattle Fishermen's Memorial 02.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Corner of the memorial's base and the adjacent wall]]
Ronald Petty's ''Seattle Fishermen's Memorial'' is installed at Docks 8 and 9 at Seattle's [[Fishermen's Terminal]]. The monument features a {{Convert|30|ft|m|adj=on}} cast stone column supporting a [[Bronze sculpture|bronze]] standing male figure, who holds a fishing line in his proper right hand. A fish is attached to the end of the line. The column's base is a bronze relief depicting 32 "sea creatures", including fish. Adjacent to the column is a concrete wall with bronze plaques displaying the names of around 460 Seattle fishermen who died since 1900.<ref name=SI/>
==History== [[File:Seattle Fishermen's Memorial 01.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Wreath in memory of the dead of the ''Arctic Rose'', 2007]]
The memorial was designed in 1987 to "honor commercial fishermen from the Seattle area who have been lost at sea". It was dedicated on October 8, 1988. The sculpture was surveyed and deemed "well maintained" by the [[Smithsonian Institution]]'s "[[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]]" program in January 1994. It is administered by the Seattle Fishermen's Memorial Foundation.<ref name=SI/>
